description: For sale: $219,900. NEW 2 bedroom, 1 bath, about 1000 sq.ft. log-sided home up the Sawbill just outside Tofte.  Cute, Affordable, Fun!  Large 2-sided deck, 380 sq ft!  Kitchen is roomy and awaiting your creations: includes smudge resistant stainless steel gas stove, refrigerator, dishwasher, custom armoire, large kitchen island, and loads of kitchen cabinets.  Sweet gas fireplace is cozy in winter and makes movie or date night that much better.  Also, it's a reliable back up to the 95% efficient gas furnace.  That furnace has already proved itself this past winter just barely sipping at the propane tank.  High quality lifetime warranty vinyl plank flooring.  Located on 1 acre lot with 2.3 million acres of State Land and Superior National Forest abutting the back property line, right out the back door! Hiking, Mt Biking and XC skiing extremely close. Spur trail to snowmobile system very handy.  Easy year round access in quiet neighborhood with seasonal views of Lake Superior and Carlton Peak.  Fully heated and insulated mini-basement with 2" x 8" walls on a cement slab: store ATV, canoes, kayaks, bikes, lawn equipment, etc.  All the fun of Tofte is a few minutes away: restaurants, Tofte 4th of July, Sawtooth Outfitters, etc.  Head north on the Sawbill Tr and explore miles of back roads or dead-end at the BWCA, unload the canoe and packs, disappear for a few days or weeks!  Upon return, roll back to the brand new house - nothing to do, except dream of the next adventure.  Hard to find such a clean home, project free in Cook County at an affordable price. Jump on this one and hunker down in the Great Northwoods: pure air, clean water, no crowds, just simple country living.

description: For sale: $699,900. Beautifully, well-maintained home with unparalleled views of Lake Superior that take your breath away.  A nice mix of Boreal Forest surrounds the home for a very serene and a quiet locale filled with wildlife. Light pours into the home, accenting the Scandinavian looking aspen panelling throughout the home with vaulted ceilings. A stunning accent is the Vermont Casting Wood Stove that was recently installed a year ago.  The kitchen has an open feel of the vaulted ceilings with large floor to ceiling windows bringing the glorious outdoor foliage and woods into your dining experience.  It's wet bar extension is ideal for the chef in the family to have the extra area for cooking and counter space, along with having a JennAir stove top with convenient conversion to a grill top.   Magnificent location with accessible ledge rock by the Big Lake that would be perfect to have a campfire as you watch the Tofte fire works in the summer months.  Dining in the gazebo whether for breakfast or dinner is a surreal experience of being surrounded by nature with the sapphire blue of Lake Superior as its backdrop.  There are many perks to this property along with it being professionally landscaped, with well established wild flowers, with five varieties 8+ foot tall azaleas that bring an amazing aura of wellbeing when strolling the property from spring to fall that is self-maintained ...no need for owning a lawn mower for this yard. A Must See!

description: For sale: $79,900. Chateau LeVeaux has been a Lake Superior destination for owners and guests since 1972. Located near Lutsen and nestled in the heart of the Sawtooth Mountain Ridge, come and enjoy this cozy and relaxing lakefront condo. This 1 BD 1 BA unit is only a stones throw from breathtaking Lake Superior. This condo has had a total makeover and comes totally furnished. Step outside this turnkey unit to a private patio offering mindfulness activities as you take in the lake. Come and enjoy the accessable shared shoreline and HOA amenities including: buit in BBQ's for grilling, large outdoor deck to chill out on, indoor pool, sauna, hot tub, game room, play area for kids and great room lobby to hang out in or when meeting in large groups. Established HOA offering no/low maintenance to every owner. Super affordable Lake Superior living! Head down the shore on the new bike trail, many rivers to explore and Grand Marais is only minutes away.

description: For sale: $235,900. All the charm of the 1930's with all of the modern conveniences one could want.  The current owner put so much TLC into the home since purchased such as a brand new bathroom, newer appliances, a new set of steps to the upper part of the lot (which overlooks its own waterfall!), fireplace improvements, improved/repaired chimney, an absolutely adorable finished shed that was used as a small art gallery, a new fenced-in area, incredible gardens.  The hardwood floors are gorgeous, the layout is ideal and the overall feel is nothing short of cozy and calm.  The Lake Superior views are astounding, there is access to the public shoreline just across the road and access to dining, shopping and hiking/biking is right outside the door.

description: For sale: $749,900. A million dollar plus build being offered at a tremendous price due to family relocation. Like new custom designed timber frame home, with Washington State Douglas fir beams and Mortis &Tenon joinery. Eastern White Cedar exterior, Minnesota stone, and Marvin windows. Every room has forest views and some lake views, especially the sunroom and the 20 ft Great Room peak. Floors are textured tile or hickory wood throughout house. Dual fuel heat (gas and electric), in floor heat throughout, and two air exchange systems. Heated 3 car garage, huge attic suitable to finish, and electric steps to attic. Third bedroom doubles as an exercise area, with a Finnleo infrared sauna. Loft area includes private balcony, library, sitting area and complete bathroom.

description: For sale: $69,900. Great investment opportunity on Lake Superior! Great condo with private bedroom, newer tile and bathroom updates! A new owner can bring their own interior vision! Great views and location, direct access to Lake Superior fabulous ledgerock right outside of the patio door. Chateau Le Veaux is located between Lutsen and Tofte, with paved Gitchi Gumme bike trail right in front, quick drive to Superior National Golf Course and Lutsen Mountains Ski Area. Lots of natural light flows through the condo, it also features functional kitchen with breakfast bar and cozy wood burning fireplace. The walk out patio is perfect to enjoy the Lake. Shared amenities include three different staircases for accessing beautiful ledge rock shoreline, pool and sauna, hot tub, game room for rainy and cold days.

description: For sale: $159,777. Welcome to 6781 W. Highway 61 in Tofte, MN!!  Perched up on a small hill, this wonderful place offers some amazing views of Lake Superior.  It's pretty much a perfect location as it has bike trails, ski trails, the Superior Hiking Trail, Lutsen Mountain Ski Hill, Superior National Golf Course, rivers and lakes to fish or swim in, shopping, dining and sight-seeing all within a mere minutes away if not right out the front door.  Use it as your North Shore get-away or continue on with the vacation rental benefits currently enjoyed by the seller...or use it as both.  This lovely cabin/home includes all of the furnishings should one wish to keep them, the plumbing and electrical has been updated, the appliances are newer and it has a compliant septic system, too.  The layout is smart and functional, there is a wood burning stove that just adds to the coziness factor, plenty of room in the bedroom/loft for additional living & sleeping space, mature trees, native birds visiting and passing through, peacefulness in the great outdoors and a big garage to store your goods/vehicles.

description: For sale: $299,900. Gorgeous lake views from every level of this sharp Lake Superior condo. Quality finishes including granite, wood & tile floors, maple cabinets, with a cool, modern vibe. There are multiple spaces to hang out in this spacious, three-level unit with 2 bedrooms and 2.5 baths. The large windows afford wide-open views of the big lake. Amenities include jetted tub, gas FP and laundry.  Currently offered as a rental unit through Cascade Vacation Rentals; helps to offset the cost of ownership, if desired. Enjoy your time on the North Shore without any pesky chores. Your only job is to enjoy lake living, and all of the activities this area has to offer: golfing, skiing, hiking, biking, beach combing, music, shops & restaurants, plus much more. Make a showing appointment to see this stunning Aspenwood unit!

description: For sale: $184,900. This is an amazing opportunity to vacation in style and free of any hassle! 1/4 share of unit 16 at SurfSide on Lake Superior, located in Tofte. This is a middle unit, with impressive Lake Superior views from each floor. The Lower level (B Side) can be rented separately, with walk out patio to the ledgerock beach and a path to the shore lid with solar lights at night. There is 2 person whirlpool tub to soak in after a day of hiking or skiing. Convenient kitchenette completes the package, has a small fridge, microwave and coffee maker.  The main and upper levels (A Side) are perfect for families and groups. There is a spacious main level bedroom with large closet and direct access to the ¾ bath. Gourmet full kitchen, opened to the living and dining area, and overlooking Lake Superior. Cozy fireplace to take the chill off in the winter months. The whole townhome is designed with large windows and glass, to maximize the exposer to sun and light, and to take full advantage of the amazing Lake Superior views. The upper floor features a large guest bedroom, with its own deck. Check out the office area, if you absolutely have to bring work with. There is also a comfy reading and relaxing area. Every space is used and designed very thoughtfully. Enjoy recent improvements - main level living room leather sofas and lazy boy like chairs in the lower level were replaced last year.  As you walk through the main and lower level, you will feel the warmth on your feet, coming from the in-floor heating, the upper level features baseboard heaters and cozy carpet. All carpet was replaced in 2018. This unit is ready for your enjoyment Up North! There are grills on site for guests to use, fire pit area, tennis court, guest laundry services and guest services area. In addition there is luxury SPA services right on site - Waves of Superior SPA and swimming pool, with fitness room.

description: For sale: $339,900. Top notch corner Unit at the premier Bluefin Bay resort, right next to the Bluefin Bay Grille! This is a rare opportunity to acquire one of Bluefin's best - only steps away from Lake Superior. Amazing big pine serves as a good buffer between the unit and the restaurant. Super functional floor plan and many updates throughout, including newer furniture and appliances. Check out the Pella windows with built in blinds! Makes it a breeze to enjoy the amazing Lake Views from both levels! Super functional kitchen open to the living room and combined with the dining area, makes for easy entertaining while cooking. Step out to the nice deck and enjoy a glass of coffee in the morning, enjoying the sound of the waves. Or go for a stroll on the beach right from your deck! Main level bedroom has separate front door and direct access to the main level bathroom. Nice and private, if you are looking for your own little place.  Master Suite completes the package, with high ceilings and exposed beams, private balcony, private Master Bathroom with 2 person air tub and views of the Lake. This townhome is a rare opportunity, it is a must see!

description: For sale: $399,900. Dream Home! Very comfortable home located in Tofte with amazing Lake Superior views. High quality built home, features Loft Style Master Suite. Once you enter the home through very welcoming porch with designated breezy seating area, you will be wowed by the views. Gourmet kitchen which will satisfy the fussiest chefs, with kitchen island and breakfast bar for quick meals. There is plenty of area for dining table, if you wanted to have one - the current owners have it set up as conversation seating area. The living room is where you want to be to relax, enjoy the views - the best part is the fireplace with built in seating benches on each side. The rest of the main level has a full bathroom and guest bedroom, which could be used as a main level Master bedroom as well. The lower level is a walk out - offers rec room and another bedroom. Games are on during the rainy days. There is a sweet patio for relaxing evening gatherings in the warm summer and fall days.

description: For sale: $275,000. Unit 32 at Bluefin Bay is a romantic retreat for your family and friends. The kitchen has been recently remodeled with beautiful custom cabinetry, granite counter-tops, and new appliances. Unit 32's living room puts you right at Lake Superior's shoreline.  Listen to the waves lapping as you keep cozy by the custom fireplace.  You can't get any closer to the lake than this. The full bathroom features a double Jacuzzi tub with a private window that allows you to relax and soak in the North Shore beauty and tranquility that only Lake Superior provides. This One Bedroom unit is part of Bluefin Bay's award-winning rental management program and grosses $50,000 in annual rental income, helping to offset the costs of ownership. There simply is no better way to own a piece of Lake Superior. The pull-out couch allows a family and friends to stay comfortably in the unit.  The resort amenities and activities will provide for busy days and the lakeside deck will provide quiet evenings to unwind. Further financial information is available.

description: Recently sold: $169,000. This home checks all the boxes! Terrific Tofte/Sawbill Tr location. Just landed your dream job on the North Shore, but all the housing is too expensive or rough? Look no more. Looking for an affordable getaway? Bam, right here. Vacation Rental income interests you? Perfect locale! Quality, beauty and efficiency meet affordability in this "just the right size" home. In the heart of the North Shore: skiing, fishing, hiking, golfing, snowmobiling, Boundary Waters are all within minutes. The comfortable, fresh, open floor plan provides the perfect living space. Outside are thousands of acres of public forest/rec land nearly adjacent. One of the last private drives off the Sawbill Trail, just below Carlton Peak, yet within a mile of scenic HWY 61. In the mood for a drink or a quick bite? Head to Coho or Bluefin Bay, just right down the road. The X/C skiing and snowmobiling trails are essentially your backyard. The Mt Bike Trails at Britton Peak are phenomenal! The builder has your pocketbook in mind: high efficiency gas furnace is on a strict diet, yet keeps it all cozy even when it's upteen below! A home this clean, with all the amenities, for this price: very rare animal in our real estate forest. Check out the two decks: follow the sun, stay out of the wind, grill it up! Lovely, private, forested lot. Plenty of room for a future garage. There is no work to do inside: just start relaxing, planning, dreaming, entertaining. Start a family, host poker night, cook lefsa, hang the fish mount, or curl up with a book. We just want your home ownership goal to progress: this is the home and/or getaway that fits financially and needs no further sweat equity - it needs lives to invest in it, to make memories and fill it up!
